{"author":{"id":"f270607f232f5ea3e06daa2368d41de7674a6d0d64158946f2581dde2c4881fc"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1747208466,"nonce":"dpLQ9M7bmOZz5POrP9dA3Yl8MfA=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s6rmzDW","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6956#issuecomment-2879074518"},"message":"Not surprisingly, this issue came up during GTA 2025, too.\n\nThe problem is https://pcingola.github.io/SnpEff/snpeff/build_db/#backwards-compatible-databases, i.e., snpEff 5 now has a fallback database strategy: if it fails to find a build for its exact version, it will work its way backwards through compatible versions and see if there's a database build for these, then use the first it finds.\nThis means that with SnpEff 5.2, you might end up downloading a database of version 5.2, 5.1 *or* 5.0, and you will only know which one it is at runtime. Unfortunately, the backwards compatibility scheme is not clearly documented - it just seems that currently 5.2/5.1/5.0 are all interoperable.\n\nWe *could* make snpeff eff accept DB versions 5.2, 5.1 and 5.0, but for each new version we would have to check the compatibility check again. Any better ideas than that?","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1747208519,"nonce":"6t0+U7m6LOUZF3aLo39tgRSnk8s=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOAW4Y0s6rmzDWzmbit00"},"target":"2527ed8b327e56c7fd0537a743c26e17a9ceca5afb004fb12ca127e42ceac2ac","message":"Not surprisingly, this issue came up during GTA 2025, too.\n\nThe problem is https://pcingola.github.io/SnpEff/snpeff/build_db/#backwards-compatible-databases, i.e., snpEff 5 now has a fallback database strategy: if it fails to find a build for its exact version, it will work its way backwards through compatible versions and see if there's a database build for these, then use the first it finds.\nThis means that with SnpEff 5.2, you might end up downloading a database of version 5.2, 5.1 *or* 5.0, and you will only know which one it is at runtime. Unfortunately, the backwards compatibility scheme is not clearly documented - it just seems that currently 5.2/5.1/5.0 are all interoperable.\n\nWe *could* make snpeff eff accept DB versions 5.2, 5.1 and 5.0, but for each new version we would have to check the compatibility range again. Any better ideas than that?","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1747208760,"nonce":"doOESGGE1B8Ia2I8YNiAeuSoNu0=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s6rm2os","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6956#issuecomment-2879089196"},"message":"@pcingola maybe you can shed some light on whether the intention is to keep backwards compatibility within the 5 series of snpEff, or on how we might detect the compatibility range for a given version? Your help would be really appreciated!","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1759698373,"nonce":"Z+/wEihExx2duHM89xv7N2QLpn4=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s7I0-RM","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6956#issuecomment-3369329740"},"message":"@jennaj I hope all issues with SnpEff 5 are fixed now.\nSpecifically, we solved\n1. the issue of inaccessible databases by pointing upstream bioconda versions to the new source (https://github.com/bioconda/bioconda-recipes/pull/59438). This triggered also a rebuild of the singularity containers that .org uses fixing this aspect automatically for you.\n2. the other issue of SnpEff wrapper versions not understanding which DB versions they are compatible with is fixed in #7295.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1759698431,"nonce":"wa/46S1Ylrj/9ZOj7Q4a6DDp5Js=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOAW4Y0s7I0-RMzn2Cd2w"},"target":"b4c67234ddaf6ee954f9fbde398d23e52afb7386b17cc7f59ec61b78d6e7c12e","message":"@jennaj I hope all issues with SnpEff 5 are fixed now.\nSpecifically, we solved\n1. the issue of inaccessible databases by pointing upstream bioconda versions to the new source (https://github.com/bioconda/bioconda-recipes/pull/59438). This triggered also a rebuild of the singularity containers that .org uses fixing this aspect automatically for you.\n2. the other issue of SnpEff wrapper versions not understanding which DB versions they are compatible with is fixed in #7295. To get that fix you need to install the latest 5.2+galaxy1 tools on .org.","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1759698675,"nonce":"8pdHtnztMabaWi3Z09gS7zWelYU=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOAW4Y0s7I0-RMzn2Cg5E"},"target":"b4c67234ddaf6ee954f9fbde398d23e52afb7386b17cc7f59ec61b78d6e7c12e","message":"@jennaj I hope all issues with SnpEff 5 are fixed now.\nSpecifically, we solved\n1. the issue of inaccessible databases by pointing upstream bioconda versions to the new source (https://github.com/bioconda/bioconda-recipes/pull/59438). This triggered also a rebuild of the singularity containers that .org uses fixing this aspect automatically for you.\n2. the other issue of SnpEff wrapper versions not understanding which DB versions they are compatible with is fixed in #7295. To get that fix you need to install the latest 5.2+galaxy1 tools on .org. On .eu we just installed that new version over the weekend and it seems to work just fine.","files":null}]}